                                Constructor
                    ========================================

1. it is a special method in java which is used to initialize current class instance variable.
2.  Constructor name should  be same as class name.
3.Constructor will not have any return type (not even void).

Note: If we write any return type for the constructor then it will become method .

Syntax:

Class Demo{
    Demo(){
        
            }
}

Note:At the time of object creation our class Constructor will be executed . Constructor is mandatory to create the object.
Note: If we don't write the constructor then java compiler adding one default constructor to our class.
How to check: we can check by using below command .
        >>>  javap classname

--> if we write constructor in the class , then compiler will not add any constructor.

Constructor are of 2 types--->
=========================
1.Zero paramterized Constructor/Default constructor

--> Constructor without parameter
         class student{
                student(){
        
              }
          }

2.Paramterized Constructor 

Constructor which contains 1 or more parameters
      class student{
                student(int a, int b){
        
              }
          }

